The Yobe State Committee on the prevention and control of the spread of corona virus has extended the work from home order to civil servants from grade level 1-12 to April 30the 2020. Briefing Journalists shortly after the committee’s meeting chaired by the state deputy governor Hon. Idi Barde Gubana, commissioner of information Hon. Abdullahi Bego said the committee has also movement into and out of the state should remained restricted. Bego said, “The stay-at-home and work-from-home directive for civil servants from Grade Level 12 and below has been extended until April 30th.” He said “In view of the ongoing prevalence of COVID-19 in certain parts of the country, movement into and out of the state, especially across our borders with Bauchi and Jigawa States, will remain restricted. The security agencies, especially the police, civil defence and vigilantes, will continue to enforce the restriction.” The commissioner emphasized.” The committee according to him thanked God that the Yobe did not record any confirmed case said People across the state should continue to observe and implement all measures against COVID-19, including social distancing, regular hand washing, and excellent respiratory etiquette. Bego maintained thatd People should also continue to pray to Almighty Allah (SWT) for protection from the disease, from other health and security challenges, and provide economic prosperity to our state and the nation in general. “The Committee also expresses its gratitude to all the corporate organisations and individuals who have made contributions to the State COVID-19 Support account.” Hon. Abdullahi Bego also expressed gratitude to all the corporate organisations and individuals who have made contributions to the State COVID-19 Support account.